MCP TECHNICAL WRAPPER SPEC
A unified context framework for persistent, role-aware intelligence.

I. System Overview
The MCP wrapper connects all Triad nodes:
• PaintBrain7 — Frontend UI and data collector  
• IDEA-HUB — Backend orchestration and document export  
• Triad-Documents — Shared Google API integration  
• MPC Server — Context persistence and memory coordination  

II. Core Components
• Context Memory Layer – Stores and recalls prior state  
• Role Manager – Assigns tone and function per agent  
• Prompt Router – Directs queries to the correct node  
• Persistence Bridge – Syncs with Google Docs and local Markdown  

III. Human ↔ LLM Mirroring
Each Markdown file = LLM-readable local record.  
Each Google Doc = human-readable live document.  
Sync loop via Triad-Documents API using Google service account.  

IV. Expansion
Planned modules: Contextual Memory (MPC), Vision & Voice Agents, Distributed Task Manager.
